$ ./iheart-mplayer.py -h
usage: iheart-mplayer.py [-h] [-s TERMS] [-l TERMS] [-p {mplayer,vlc}]
                         [-o PLAYER_OPTIONS] [-t STREAM_TYPE] [-v]
                         [stream_id]

Play an iHeartRadio station in mplayer or VLC

positional arguments:
  stream_id             The (five-digit?) ID number of the station

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -s TERMS, --search TERMS
                        List station search results for TERMS
  -l TERMS, --lucky TERMS
                        "I'm feeling lucky" search for TERMS (play the first
                        result)
  -p {mplayer,vlc}, --player {mplayer,vlc}
                        The player to use (currently either mplayer or vlc),
                        the default is mplayer
  -o PLAYER_OPTIONS, --player-options PLAYER_OPTIONS
                        Command-line arguments to pass the media player,
                        should be a quoted string beginning with a space. Yes,
                        this is ugly, blame argparse.
  -t STREAM_TYPE, --stream-type STREAM_TYPE
                        The type of stream to use, currently either auto or
                        one of shout, rtmp, stw, or pls. The default is auto.
  -v, --verbose         Display extra information

Station IDs can be obtained with the search function (-s), or from the URL
you'll get if you find a station on the website; for instance the ID for this
URL is 5361:

http://www.iheart.com/live/News-Talk-760-5361/
